The paper proposes a new approach for inverse reinforcement learning using deep Gaussian processes, which is a machine learning technique. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed approach is tested on benchmark tests, which involve robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely category. The paper also deals with learning abstract representations of state feature space, which is related to computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with control systems, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
